        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme “Assistance for Protected Cultivation” by the Agriculture and Co-operation Department, Government of Gujarat aims to promote modern, climate-resilient horticulture practices by providing financial support for protected cultivation infrastructure like mulching, nursery development, and plug nurseries. The scheme encourages self-employment and sustainable income generation for farmers through the use of polyhouses, shed net houses, and starter kits to improve crop productivity and resource efficiency. \n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "> **Plastic Cover (Mulching):**\n\n\n\n  - **General Area:** ₹32,000/- per hectare.  - **Hilly Area:** ₹36,800/- per hectare.  - 50% of the expenditure incurred, limited to 1 hectare per beneficiary.\n  - **Self-Employment Oriented Horticulture Nursery Development Programme:**\n  - **Nursery Structure:** ₹3,50,000/- per unit   - ₹3,00,000/- per unit for 500 sq.m. area\n  - **Starter Kit:** ₹50,000/- per unit  - Assistance up to 65% of the cost or ₹2,27,500/-, whichever is less.\n\n\n> **Shed Net House &amp; Polyhouse:**\n\n\n\n  - **Coverage:** 500 sq.m to 4,000 sq.m  - Assistance as per square meter cost based on empanelled company prices\n  - Structures supported: Cylindrical, bamboo, and wooden.\n\n\n> **Plug Nursery:**\n\n\n\n  - **Public sector:** ₹30,00,000/- per hectare for 1 hectare  - **Private sector:** Assistance of 50% or ₹15,00,000/- per hectare (whichever is less) for 1 hectare.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme “Assistance for Protected Cultivation” by the Agriculture and Co-operation Department, Government of Gujarat aims to promote protected horticulture practices by providing financial assistance to farmers for mulching, plug nursery, polyhouse, shed net house, and nursery development.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
        "detailedDescription": [
